properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 31 at 2:08PM PST until February 2 at 3:00AM PST by NWS San Francisco CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, northwest winds 20 to 30 kt with
gusts up to 40 kt and seas 11 to 13 feet at 13 seconds
expected. For the Small Craft Advisory, northwest winds 10 to
20 kt with gusts up to 30 kt expected. For the Storm Watch,
northwest winds 30 to 40 kt with gusts up to 55 kt and seas 10
to 15 feet at 13 seconds possible.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters from Point Pinos to Point Piedras
Blancas California out to 10 nm.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 9 PM Saturday to 3 AM PST
Sunday. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 2 PM to 9 PM PST
Saturday. For the Storm Watch, from late Saturday night
through Sunday evening.

* IMPACTS...Very strong winds will cause hazardous seas which
could capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should prepare to remain in port, alter course, and/or
secure the vessel for severe conditions before conditions
deteriorate.
